article.headline: Ark.-Little Rock 83, Texas State 77
article.story: SAN MARCOS, Texas (AP) -- Rashad Jones-Jennings scored 25 points and grabbed 20 rebounds to help Arkansas-Little Rock defeat Texas State 83-77 on Wednesday night. Terrance Akins added 18 points and Byron Ray had 10 rebounds for the Trojans (3-2). UALR used a 6-0 run to start the second half and take a 41-37 lead on a 3-pointer by Akins with 17:50 left. Charles Dotson led Texas State (1-3) with 16 points and five rebounds. Matt Fullenwider scored 12 points, Brandon Bush had 10 and Brandon Thomas had seven rebounds for the Bobcats. Texas State scored 25 points off 17 Trojan turnovers.
